The rocket stands at 118 meters (387 feet) tall and weighs over 400,000 kilograms (880,000 pounds) at launch. It is renowned for its reusability, meaning that its components can be used multiple times, reducing the cost and environmental impact of space exploration. 

The Falcon 9 is used to launch satellites, deliver cargo to the International Space Station, and perform other commercial and government missions. It has been in operation since 2010 and has undergone several upgrades and iterations.
